1 shal l be eligible for reappointment. Provided that, a member of the
2 Board shall serve no more than two consecutive terms and any
3 unexpired term that a member is appointed to shall not apply to this
4 limit. The Governor shall appoint the necessary members to the
5 Board upon vacancies and immediately prior to the expiration of the
6 various terms. Upon request of the Governor, appointments of a
7 licensed embalmer and funeral director member of the Board shall be
8 made from a list of five qualified persons submitted by the Oklahoma
9 Funeral Directors Association. An appointment to fill a vacancy
10 shall be for the unexpired term. A member of the Board shall serve
11 until a successor is appointed and qualified. No person shall be a
12 member of the Board, unless, at the time of appointment, the person
13 is of good moral character and a resident of this state. Five of
14 the members shall have been actively engaged in the practice of
15 embalming and funeral directing in this state for not less than
16 seven (7) consecutive years immediately prior to the appointment of
17 the person, shall have an active license as provided by the Funeral
18 Services Licensing Act, shall keep the license effective, and remain
19 a resident of this state during the entire time the person serves on
20 the Board. Two of the members of the Board shall be chosen from the
21 general public, one of whom shall, if possible, be a person licensed
22 and actively engaged in the health care field, and shall not be
23 licensed funeral directors or embalmers or have any interest,
24 directly or indirectly, in any funeral establishment or any business
